<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="248" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,151,413]" pageId="1" pageNumber="248">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,188,213]" pageId="1" pageNumber="248">Remarks.</emphasis>
It is difficult to distinguish this genus from related genera because coloration and head structure are very similar. However, the characteristics of the male genitalia are clearly different; generally the aedeagal shaft is tubular and elongate with paired processes or flanges and the pygofer has processes. 
<taxonomicName box="[1093,1205,254,278]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Fistulatus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="248" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1093,1205,254,278]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="248">Fistulatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resembles the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Distant" authorityName="Distant" box="[151,318,287,312]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Kutara" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="248" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,231,289,312]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="248">Kutara</emphasis>
Distant
</taxonomicName>
but differs in having male pygofer processes. 
<taxonomicName box="[837,949,288,312]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Fistulatus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="248" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[837,949,288,312]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="248">Fistulatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is related to the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Distant" authorityName="Distant" box="[1208,1393,287,312]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Carvaka" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="248" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1208,1304,288,312]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="248">Carvaka</emphasis>
Distant
</taxonomicName>
but differ from the latter by aedeagus usually lacking apical paired processes. This genus is also similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Distant" authorityName="Distant" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Bhatia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="248" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1361,1436,321,345]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="248">Bhatia</emphasis>
Distant
</taxonomicName>
but can be differentiated from the latter by lacking aedeagal basal process and appendages between aedeagus and connective.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
